CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 7, 1972, pg. 9 reads: "Aid Sickle Cell - Mrs. Lelia Lucas, president of the Excelsior Art Club of Clairton (left), presents a check to Mrs. Connie Wheeler for the Black Athletes Foundation, as the Rev. J. Rosamond Key of Clairton's Morning Star Baptist Church looks on. Mrs. Wheeler is a secretary for th Black Athletes Foundation. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: President of Excelsior Art Club Lelia Lucas presenting check to Connie Wheeler for the Black Athletes Foundation, with Rev. J. Rosamond Key looking on, in Morning Star Baptist Church, Clairton
